1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:48,424
CHAPTER 8: I'M SURE IT WAS MY GLASSES
YOU TROD ON EARLIER

2
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:54,054
EPISODE 3

3
00:00:58,142 --> 00:01:00,311
Looks like he's on his way
to catch the bus.

4
00:01:01,645 --> 00:01:04,690
Am I going to run into him
every time I go to school?

5
00:01:06,859 --> 00:01:08,944
He's a teacher. He should leave earlier.

6
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:22,750
Get a move on.

7
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:37,973
What's he doing?

8
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:52,863
Mr. Ga!

9
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:55,574
Mr. Ga!

10
00:01:56,909 --> 00:01:59,036
Mr. Ga! Are you okay?

11
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:00,371
Mr. Ga!

12
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,082
Mr. Ga!

13
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:09,505
What's that?

14
00:02:10,089 --> 00:02:11,257
Is that bird poop?

15
00:02:13,175 --> 00:02:15,135
Gross!

16
00:02:27,690 --> 00:02:29,275
Mr. Ga?

17
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,277
Mr. Ga!

18
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,361
Mr. Ga.

19
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:33,988
Sir…

20
00:02:37,116 --> 00:02:38,576
I don't think he's breathing.

21
00:02:43,873 --> 00:02:46,208
Mr. Ga! Wake up.

22
00:02:46,292 --> 00:02:47,293
What do I do?

23
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:51,171
Mr. Ga!

24
00:02:53,007 --> 00:02:55,092
Man, he is not breathing!

25
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:56,468
What do I do?

26
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:08,981
Come on, Eui-ju.

27
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:12,234
You're doing this to save a life.

28
00:03:21,327 --> 00:03:22,202
Mr. Ga?

29
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:24,538
Mr. Ga.

30
00:03:25,164 --> 00:03:26,582
Are you okay?

31
00:03:26,665 --> 00:03:27,499
Mr. Ga.

32
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:30,252
Are you…

33
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,839
It's me, sir. Yeo Eui-ju.

34
00:03:34,798 --> 00:03:35,758
Are you okay?

35
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:47,394
What are you doing here?

36
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:51,357
What do you mean?

37
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:54,109
How can you say that to the person
who just saved your life?

38
00:03:54,777 --> 00:03:57,780
Anyway, why did you pass out here?

39
00:03:57,863 --> 00:04:00,950
Surely not just because
of some pigeon poop?

40
00:04:03,953 --> 00:04:07,206
Pigeon droppings not only carry avian flu
and other infectious diseases,

41
00:04:07,289 --> 00:04:10,209
but also contain ammonia and acids
strong enough to damage concrete.

42
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:11,752
"Just because"?

43
00:04:16,215 --> 00:04:17,299
Have you lost something?

44
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:19,885
Oh, your glasses.

45
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:21,929
Shall I help you look?

46
00:04:23,514 --> 00:04:24,348
Sure.

47
00:04:24,974 --> 00:04:25,933
Okay.

48
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,419
What was that sound?

49
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:54,837
Did you just step on my glasses?

50
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:57,548
No.

51
00:04:57,631 --> 00:04:59,299
No, don't be silly.

52
00:05:00,134 --> 00:05:02,469
I was just…

53
00:05:03,554 --> 00:05:04,847
I mean…

54
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:07,099
I just stepped on a branch, that's all.

55
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:10,019
-That was the crack of it snapping.
-What time is it?

56
00:05:10,102 --> 00:05:11,854
-Sorry?
-What time is it?

57
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:18,610
It's 7:40 a.m.

58
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:21,572
Will you call Dong-ju?

59
00:05:24,283 --> 00:05:25,117
Sure.

60
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:29,204
It's locked.

61
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:31,749
Okay.

62
00:05:32,416 --> 00:05:33,459
Here you are.

63
00:05:34,752 --> 00:05:36,503
Is your vision that bad?

64
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:38,881
It's me.

65
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:42,885
If you go to my room, my spare glasses
are in the first drawer of my desk.

66
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,011
Can you bring them to me?

67
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:47,056
Yeah, I'm near the bus stop.

68
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,058
Okay.

69
00:05:51,727 --> 00:05:52,811
Where have they gotten to?

70
00:05:58,025 --> 00:06:01,653
I told you to carpool with us.
Ignoring me always leads to trouble.

71
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:04,156
What do I do?

72
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:05,866
Shall I just chuck them somewhere?

73
00:06:10,329 --> 00:06:11,205
Oh, I found 500 won!

74
00:06:12,414 --> 00:06:13,957
Come on!

75
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,168
Let's go or we'll be late.

76
00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:19,505
If we haven't found them by now,
they're not here.

77
00:06:20,422 --> 00:06:23,926
I'm sure someone saw them and took them.

78
00:06:24,009 --> 00:06:25,886
They recognized how expensive they were.

79
00:06:25,969 --> 00:06:27,513
-Don't you think?
-Yes.

80
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:28,639
-Yes.
-Right?

81
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,392
See you at school.

82
00:06:40,359 --> 00:06:41,443
What's with that look?

83
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:50,160
Is she hoping for a lift?

84
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:04,341
Darn it.

85
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:06,635
Sorry, it's so cramped.

86
00:07:07,511 --> 00:07:10,097
No, it's fine.

87
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:11,515
I'm just grateful for the lift.

88
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,568
THIS IS CRAZY!

89
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,612
This is crazy!
I'm in the teachers' car right now.

90
00:07:25,696 --> 00:07:28,407
Mr. Jung's driving, and I'm stuck between
Mr. Noh and Mr. Yoon.

91
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:29,366
No way!

92
00:07:33,871 --> 00:07:34,872
How'd that happen?

93
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:38,709
There was a whole thing.
I'll tell you later.

94
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:43,881
I'm putting my seat back.

95
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:48,677
Okay.

96
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:54,099
I knew it.

97
00:07:54,183 --> 00:07:58,353
Mr. Ga knows no one but himself
and sweet Mr. Yoon doesn't say anything.

98
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,858
Were you up all night again?

99
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,530
It's because you wouldn't let him sleep.

100
00:08:08,614 --> 00:08:11,867
-Don't you know he's a sleepyhead?
-I didn't do it on purpose.

101
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:14,912
He wanted another round. That's all.

102
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:17,497
It doesn't matter
how much you're enjoying it,

103
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:18,790
make sure he gets his rest.

104
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:20,125
Got it?

105
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:22,669
Unbelievable!

106
00:08:22,753 --> 00:08:24,713
What can they have been doing all night?

107
00:08:25,214 --> 00:08:28,008
God, forgive me.

108
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:30,219
I'll go to hell after writing this!

109
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:37,142
What's wrong?

110
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,562
Are you hot? Shall I put the AC on?

111
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:41,980
No.

112
00:08:42,898 --> 00:08:44,233
There's no need.

113
00:08:49,905 --> 00:08:51,990
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

114
00:08:57,246 --> 00:08:59,289
Who are you to ride in his car?

115
00:08:59,373 --> 00:09:01,583
Cat got your tongue? Answer me!

116
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:04,586
-Say something!
-How dare you!

117
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:08,715
What's wrong with her?

118
00:09:09,925 --> 00:09:11,093
Just a moment, sir.

119
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:12,261
If they see me in here,

120
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:14,513
they're going to kill me.

121
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:16,723
Hey, it's Mr. Jung!

122
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:21,270
No, this can't be happening.

123
00:09:21,353 --> 00:09:22,604
No!

124
00:09:22,688 --> 00:09:25,315
If the other kids find out I'm here,
I'm dead meat.

125
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,358
What do I do?

126
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:35,761
I need more oxygen.

127
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:46,605
I can't say that didn't hurt.

128
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,149
Still, he saved my life.

129
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:57,449
It's because you wouldn't let me sleep.

130
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,951
You know I'm a sleepyhead.

131
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:04,831
They're the one true pair.

132
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:16,593
Aren't you getting out?

133
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:22,140
Hey.

134
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:23,934
Yes?

135
00:11:25,977 --> 00:11:26,937
Tell me the truth.

136
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,147
About what?

137
00:11:30,107 --> 00:11:32,109
Whichever way I look at it,

138
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:34,986
I'm sure it was my glasses
you trod on earlier.

139
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:37,072
No, it wasn't.

140
00:11:39,324 --> 00:11:42,160
If you're lying to me,
you're going to regret it.

141
00:11:42,744 --> 00:11:44,871
I'm really not.

142
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:47,958
-Where's your essay?
-I'm working on it.

143
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:58,260
CHAPTER 9:
HI! I'M JENNY

144
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:01,847
-Good morning, Mr. Ga!
-Good morning, Mr. Ga!

145
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:04,558
Come in.

146
00:12:04,641 --> 00:12:06,226
-Who is it?
-A transfer?

147
00:12:12,983 --> 00:12:16,862
We have an exchange student joining us
for the rest of the semester.

148
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:22,993
Hi! I'm Jenny.

149
00:12:23,827 --> 00:12:26,705
I'm here on exchange from Singapore.

150
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:28,457
Nice to meet you all.

151
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:31,209
I'm really excited to be here, so

152
00:12:31,293 --> 00:12:33,462
I hope we'll have a lot of fun together.

153
00:12:35,672 --> 00:12:36,923
Welcome, Jenny!

154
00:12:37,424 --> 00:12:38,425
She's so cute.

155
00:12:38,508 --> 00:12:39,342
You can sit there.

156
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:44,890
-Hey, Jenny.
-Hello.

157
00:12:44,973 --> 00:12:46,099
Hello.

158
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:49,144
Hello.

159
00:12:50,562 --> 00:12:51,605
Hi!

160
00:12:56,443 --> 00:12:59,613
She's probably not used to Korean culture
or Korean schools,

161
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:00,864
so look after her.

162
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:02,073
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

163
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:03,158
Dismissed.

164
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,785
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

165
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:08,246
Jenny.

166
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:10,373
-Hi!
-Hello!

167
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:11,833
Hello!

168
00:13:11,917 --> 00:13:13,835
-Hey!
-Hello!

169
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:16,171
My name is Yeo Eui-ju.

170
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:17,547
Do you speak Korean well?

171
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:20,926
Yes. Okay, maybe like…

172
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:23,220
I can't speak that much Korean.

173
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:24,971
But I'm learning.

174
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:27,849
If you help me,
I'm sure I'll soon pick it up.

175
00:13:29,059 --> 00:13:31,144
My name is Go-ya.

176
00:13:31,228 --> 00:13:32,187
Nice to meet you.

177
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,439
Nice to meet you.

178
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:39,736
Jenny, why did you come to Korea?

179
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,490
Doesn't everybody want to come to Korea?

180
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:45,784
There's lots of yummy food.

181
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:49,746
And I wanted to visit the places
I've seen in K-dramas.

182
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,831
-I see.
-That's right.

183
00:13:51,915 --> 00:13:53,291
That makes sense.

184
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:58,129
Then why did you come to Jeonju
and not Seoul?

185
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:01,925
I did apply to a school in Seoul.

186
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:03,260
But…

187
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:04,970
I was on the computer, and I was like…

188
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:09,766
I clicked on the wrong one.

189
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,059
-You…
-You clicked on the wrong…

190
00:14:11,142 --> 00:14:12,936
-Oh, she clicked on the wrong one!
-Oh, she clicked on the wrong one!

191
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,771
You selected this school by mistake.

192
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:18,358
But it's okay. This place is great, like…

193
00:14:18,441 --> 00:14:19,901
Jeonju is really pretty.

194
00:14:19,985 --> 00:14:22,279
-Yeah, it really is.
-It's great!

195
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:26,157
CHAPTER 10:
I'M GOING TO TUMBLE YOU AROUND

196
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:29,286
Darn it.

197
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:36,418
Is it because he switched glasses?

198
00:14:38,795 --> 00:14:40,130
Why does he look sick?

199
00:14:49,139 --> 00:14:50,974
Why won't this stick?

200
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,935
Shall I just throw them away
and feign ignorance?

201
00:14:56,271 --> 00:14:57,814
I can't do that.

202
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,608
I have to give them back.

203
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:02,944
It seems like his spare ones
aren't the right strength.

204
00:15:04,863 --> 00:15:07,449
Come on, help me out here.

205
00:15:07,532 --> 00:15:09,326
Type one verbs

206
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:13,872
refers to almost all verbs
that do not end in "ru."

207
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:16,625
So, the verb "iku" will become "ikanai."

208
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,668
You add "a" to the "ku" form.

209
00:15:18,752 --> 00:15:20,629
Type two verbs are much easier.

210
00:15:20,712 --> 00:15:22,464
All you have to do is take off the "ru."

211
00:15:24,174 --> 00:15:27,052
So it will become "tabenai."

212
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:29,804
As for type three verbs…

213
00:15:35,018 --> 00:15:39,064
I'M TRULY SORRY

214
00:15:46,613 --> 00:15:48,198
JAPANESE LANGUAGE

215
00:15:52,702 --> 00:15:54,871
During my class…

216
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:59,668
You're not paying attention to me?

217
00:16:01,711 --> 00:16:03,338
I cannot believe it.

218
00:16:15,517 --> 00:16:16,351
How are you feeling?

219
00:16:17,435 --> 00:16:20,271
Like I've been watching
the Mandelbrot set zooming out

220
00:16:21,064 --> 00:16:22,941
at ultra-high speed all day.

221
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:24,609
Mandel…

222
00:16:26,778 --> 00:16:27,862
I said I feel dizzy.

223
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:31,866
I see.

224
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:38,665
Come in.

225
00:16:47,424 --> 00:16:49,175
I caught one of your students

226
00:16:49,259 --> 00:16:53,054
doing homework you assigned
during my Japanese class.

227
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,849
You deal with it, Mr. Ga.

228
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:05,984
Read it.

229
00:17:06,568 --> 00:17:07,819
Sorry?

230
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,740
Can't you just read it?

231
00:17:11,823 --> 00:17:13,658
All the other teachers are here.

232
00:17:24,127 --> 00:17:25,420
"Dear Euclid."

233
00:17:26,171 --> 00:17:27,213
I can't hear you.

234
00:17:29,716 --> 00:17:30,717
"Hello."

235
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:34,262
"I…

236
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:38,975
live in Jeonju in the year 2026,

237
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:42,562
and my name is Yeo Eui-ju,
and I am 18 years old."

238
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:49,319
"When I was in seventh grade,

239
00:17:50,028 --> 00:17:53,156
I was humiliated in front of my classmates
while solving a proof problem."

240
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:55,658
"The shame of that

241
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:58,203
led me to give up on math."

242
00:17:59,162 --> 00:18:03,166
"Why were you so obsessed with proofs?"

243
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:05,960
"Are things that can't be proven
totally useless?"

244
00:18:06,544 --> 00:18:10,757
"If I'd been born before you, would I have
been spared from that kind of torment?"

245
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:16,554
Is this an apology or a complaint?

246
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:22,185
"Nevertheless,

247
00:18:22,977 --> 00:18:27,023
I can't help but admire
the first sentence of your book,

248
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:29,526
'A point is that which has no parts.'"

249
00:18:30,527 --> 00:18:34,322
"Even someone like me who gave up on math
can understand that in one go."

250
00:18:34,948 --> 00:18:36,449
"Sir,

251
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:41,579
I'm truly sorry for hurting you
with my ignorance,

252
00:18:41,663 --> 00:18:43,206
and for that I apologize…"

253
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:45,834
That's as far as I've got.

254
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:49,712
If you're going to write it during class,
don't bother. Two demerits.

255
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:52,340
What? You think that's unfair?

256
00:18:53,925 --> 00:18:55,051
No, sir.

257
00:18:56,761 --> 00:18:58,555
I think taking care of your friends

258
00:18:58,638 --> 00:19:01,474
is one of the most important things
you learn at school.

259
00:19:04,686 --> 00:19:06,521
Starting today, you take care of Ji-a.

260
00:19:06,604 --> 00:19:09,941
From now on, if Choi Ji-a is absent, late,
or not at her desk during homeroom,

261
00:19:10,024 --> 00:19:11,734
I will give her two demerit points,

262
00:19:11,818 --> 00:19:12,777
and you four.

263
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:16,573
-Sorry?
-Go.

264
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:19,284
You can't do that!

265
00:19:20,118 --> 00:19:21,119
Mr. Ga!

266
00:19:23,746 --> 00:19:25,290
I can't.

267
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:26,416
But, sir…

268
00:19:29,377 --> 00:19:30,503
Darn.

269
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,758
Wow, that's ridiculous.

270
00:19:35,842 --> 00:19:38,052
How can you get more demerits than Ji-a?

271
00:19:38,136 --> 00:19:41,180
Why does he only ever pick on you?

272
00:19:41,264 --> 00:19:42,682
That's totally unfair.

273
00:19:42,765 --> 00:19:44,475
Wait, surely not.

274
00:19:44,559 --> 00:19:45,727
Do you think he likes you?

275
00:19:48,021 --> 00:19:50,565
Or maybe you look like his ex-girlfriend?

276
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:53,192
He's picking on you
because every time he sees you,

277
00:19:53,276 --> 00:19:54,569
it reminds him of being dumped.

278
00:19:54,652 --> 00:19:56,487
What if it turns out

279
00:19:56,571 --> 00:20:00,116
your parents and his parents
are mortal enemies?

280
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:03,786
Guys, just give it a rest.

281
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:06,998
Maybe he just doesn't like your face.

282
00:20:07,081 --> 00:20:08,166
That could be it!

283
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:10,168
Hey!

284
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:13,004
Let's try something.

285
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:17,842
-Good afternoon, Mr. Ga.
-Good afternoon, Mr. Ga.

286
00:20:19,302 --> 00:20:20,511
Where did we get to last time?

287
00:20:21,512 --> 00:20:22,722
Mr. Ga,

288
00:20:23,306 --> 00:20:25,224
Eui-ju isn't feeling very well.

289
00:20:27,018 --> 00:20:27,977
What's wrong with her?

290
00:20:30,688 --> 00:20:32,732
I don't know, sir.

291
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:35,193
I feel dizzy and nauseous.

292
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:37,987
And, gosh, I'm feeling so weak.

293
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:40,531
Oh, no.

294
00:20:41,115 --> 00:20:42,325
What am I going to do?

295
00:20:42,951 --> 00:20:45,495
I can't take it.

296
00:20:45,578 --> 00:20:47,497
I think I'm dying.

297
00:20:58,424 --> 00:20:59,258
Yeo Eui-ju.

298
00:21:00,635 --> 00:21:01,719
Yes?

299
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:04,681
Define left-hand limit
and right-hand limit.

300
00:21:06,057 --> 00:21:06,933
Sorry?

301
00:21:21,948 --> 00:21:26,035
If both the left-hand and right-hand limit
exist but aren't equal, does the limit

302
00:21:26,119 --> 00:21:27,120
exist or not?

303
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:28,621
Sorry?

304
00:21:28,705 --> 00:21:30,540
If there's a single point
separated from a graph,

305
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,250
what kind of discontinuity is that?

306
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:37,130
What conditions do we need to prove
that f(x) is continuous at x equals a?

307
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:42,677
Didn't we cover this last class?

308
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,220
Were you even listening?

309
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:46,180
If you'd revised
instead of faking being sick,

310
00:21:46,264 --> 00:21:47,807
you'd be able to answer.

311
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:52,061
What are you doing here?

312
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:58,067
I thought you wanted
to take Discrete Math together.

313
00:21:58,151 --> 00:21:59,861
Cut!

314
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:08,119
Ju Si-on!

315
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:09,996
Yes?

316
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:13,166
Isn't that what I told you last time?
Were you even listening?

317
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:15,752
You guys were great.

318
00:22:16,461 --> 00:22:18,129
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

319
00:22:18,212 --> 00:22:21,591
Do you not get the meaning
between the lines?

320
00:22:23,217 --> 00:22:26,012
Here, Yoon is talking to Tae-ha,
and you're supposed to feel

321
00:22:26,095 --> 00:22:27,597
angry and jealous, but…

322
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,558
Yoon has already agreed
to take one of your classes with you.

323
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:33,269
You know
you're on a different level to Tae-ha.

324
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:36,314
You're supposed
to radiate an air of superiority!

325
00:22:36,397 --> 00:22:37,774
Are you not capable of that?

326
00:22:38,524 --> 00:22:39,567
I think I did.

327
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:44,822
How dare you answer back!

328
00:22:48,159 --> 00:22:51,162
I'm the writer,
and you're just a character.

329
00:22:51,245 --> 00:22:52,163
Get it?

330
00:22:52,246 --> 00:22:54,540
I'm the writer, and you're just a teach…

331
00:22:57,710 --> 00:22:58,544
Hang on.

332
00:23:00,171 --> 00:23:02,256
You're just a character.

333
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:06,969
Why do you always go off script
and do what you want?

334
00:23:07,053 --> 00:23:12,100
Every last period of my writing has soul!

335
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:16,729
So stop whining and do exactly what I say!

336
00:23:16,813 --> 00:23:18,272
Yes, ma'am.

337
00:23:19,482 --> 00:23:20,858
What are you fuming about?

338
00:23:28,116 --> 00:23:31,536
Write the basic concepts of functions
ten times each.

339
00:23:32,537 --> 00:23:33,704
Yes, sir.

340
00:23:38,751 --> 00:23:40,920
Mr. Full-of-regrets Ju Si-on.

341
00:23:41,003 --> 00:23:42,130
Just you wait and see.

342
00:23:42,213 --> 00:23:45,508
I'm going to tumble you around.

343
00:23:46,134 --> 00:23:47,510
Round and around.

344
00:23:47,593 --> 00:23:50,805
CHAPTER 11:
HE NEVER LIKED ME TO BEGIN WITH

345
00:23:50,888 --> 00:23:52,265
Is this a pork cutlet?

346
00:23:53,015 --> 00:23:53,975
-It's a fish cutlet.
-Jenny.

347
00:23:54,058 --> 00:23:55,977
Is the food okay?

348
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,687
-It's pretty tasty.
-It is, isn't it?

349
00:23:58,396 --> 00:24:00,773
If you enjoy it too much, you'll get fat.

350
00:24:02,692 --> 00:24:04,402
-Just eat up.
-Hey, Jenny.

351
00:24:04,986 --> 00:24:06,112
Do you have a boyfriend?

352
00:24:06,195 --> 00:24:07,530
Yes.

353
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:11,284
He's Brazilian.

354
00:24:11,367 --> 00:24:12,952
Brazilian?

355
00:24:13,035 --> 00:24:14,203
His name is Luiz.

356
00:24:14,912 --> 00:24:16,330
So global.

357
00:24:17,039 --> 00:24:18,207
How did you meet him?

358
00:24:18,791 --> 00:24:20,626
At the Louvre in Paris.

359
00:24:20,710 --> 00:24:22,253
He's studying photography at college.

360
00:24:22,336 --> 00:24:24,672
He kept asking me to be his model.

361
00:24:24,755 --> 00:24:27,175
So, that's how we started dating.

362
00:24:28,509 --> 00:24:30,261
So, he's in France right now?

363
00:24:30,344 --> 00:24:31,387
Yeah.

364
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:33,097
You must miss him.

365
00:24:33,181 --> 00:24:34,140
Yeah.

366
00:24:34,724 --> 00:24:36,184
He said since I left,

367
00:24:36,267 --> 00:24:38,978
he's completely lost his appetite.

368
00:24:39,061 --> 00:24:41,314
He said he doesn't smile much either.

369
00:24:41,939 --> 00:24:43,149
Isn't that funny?

370
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:44,901
Brazilian guys are different.

371
00:24:44,984 --> 00:24:46,319
How would you know?

372
00:24:46,402 --> 00:24:48,070
How would I not?

373
00:24:49,113 --> 00:24:53,492
Jenny, what did your boyfriend say
when he asked you to model for him?

374
00:24:54,869 --> 00:24:56,621
Excuse me.

375
00:24:57,205 --> 00:24:59,916
I've been searching for the perfect
golden hour light all day.

376
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:04,545
But I've ended up finding something
even more beautiful.

377
00:25:05,129 --> 00:25:08,966
Let me capture this beautiful moment.

378
00:25:11,469 --> 00:25:12,929
That's so romantic.

379
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:21,938
YUL EYE CLINIC

380
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:25,024
PRESCRIPTION

381
00:25:39,372 --> 00:25:44,085
BUBU PHARMACY

382
00:25:45,336 --> 00:25:47,213
There's seven days-worth.

383
00:25:47,964 --> 00:25:49,924
Take them three times a day.

384
00:25:50,007 --> 00:25:52,426
This is the anti-inflammatory
and this is for your stomach.

385
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:53,636
-Okay.
-And,

386
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:55,972
your eye medicine is a steroid,

387
00:25:56,055 --> 00:25:58,307
so make sure you shake it before use.

388
00:25:58,891 --> 00:26:00,142
That'll be 9,600 won.

389
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:04,355
Your eyes are really bloodshot.

390
00:26:04,981 --> 00:26:07,984
Since you're wearing glasses,
I guess you didn't get LASIK.

391
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:09,443
You'd better change your glasses.

392
00:26:09,527 --> 00:26:11,279
Our eyes are so important.

393
00:26:43,352 --> 00:26:44,729
I'm sorry.

394
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:48,107
I was just reminded of that thing.

395
00:26:48,190 --> 00:26:49,275
You know in cartoons,

396
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,944
when the main character
takes off their glasses,

397
00:26:52,028 --> 00:26:54,196
and they're transformed
into someone really handsome.

398
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:01,579
You really should wear lenses if you can.

399
00:27:05,374 --> 00:27:06,417
Bye!

400
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:13,466
A man straight out of a comic.

401
00:27:14,884 --> 00:27:15,926
A man straight out of a comic.

402
00:27:22,892 --> 00:27:24,518
AFTER-SCHOOL PROGRAM APPLICATION

403
00:27:24,602 --> 00:27:26,771
Get your parents' signatures
and bring it back to me.

404
00:27:26,854 --> 00:27:27,688
Yes, sir.

405
00:27:37,698 --> 00:27:38,949
What the heck?

406
00:27:39,033 --> 00:27:40,076
Is he sick?

407
00:27:42,328 --> 00:27:43,287
What did the doctor say?

408
00:27:45,831 --> 00:27:47,833
It'll take at least two weeks
to get new glasses.

409
00:27:48,334 --> 00:27:49,210
Two weeks?

410
00:27:49,877 --> 00:27:51,504
How are you going to cope for that long?

411
00:27:55,758 --> 00:27:56,717
Well done.

412
00:27:56,801 --> 00:27:58,677
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

413
00:28:07,269 --> 00:28:08,270
Ji-a!

414
00:28:08,354 --> 00:28:09,688
Ji-a, where are you going?

415
00:28:10,606 --> 00:28:12,191
You have to wait for the final bell.

416
00:28:13,442 --> 00:28:14,485
Are you off to work?

417
00:28:14,568 --> 00:28:16,237
Can't you wait until the bell rings?

418
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:19,698
From now on, if you come in late
or leave early, I will get demerits.

419
00:28:21,951 --> 00:28:22,910
Hey!

420
00:28:22,993 --> 00:28:25,371
I asked nicely.
Can't you just do me a solid?

421
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:28,916
Do you think I want to do this?

422
00:28:36,215 --> 00:28:37,633
Mr. Ga! Did you see that?

423
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,219
I clearly told Ji-a not to go.

424
00:28:40,302 --> 00:28:43,305
But she didn't listen and just left.

425
00:28:47,601 --> 00:28:50,646
Can't you just count this
as me having done it?

426
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:52,940
There's really nothing I can do.

427
00:28:55,860 --> 00:28:56,777
Yeo Eui-ju.

428
00:28:58,863 --> 00:29:00,156
Four demerit points.

429
00:29:09,165 --> 00:29:12,710
GENERAL WASTE

430
00:29:14,545 --> 00:29:15,796
Go-ya was right.

431
00:29:16,422 --> 00:29:18,048
Things were screwed up from the start.

432
00:29:18,632 --> 00:29:20,718
He just never liked me.

433
00:29:25,890 --> 00:29:28,100
I saw you filming. Delete it.

434
00:29:28,184 --> 00:29:30,811
I want you to write a letter to Euclid.
Twenty pages.

435
00:29:32,521 --> 00:29:33,397
Yeo Eui-ju.

436
00:29:34,148 --> 00:29:35,316
Four demerit points.

437
00:30:56,855 --> 00:30:58,857
Subtitle: Paul Carver

